i'm making a game as a solo dev, i want your honest, realistic opinion on it.

some facts:
1. i'm a solo dev with a family/kids and a fulltime job so my time per week is limited (~10 hours a week?)
2. i'm a senior front-end (angular) developer with 20 years of experience. i have an affinity for the front of the front-end and have a good feeling for making things look/feel good in the UI/UX department, CSS animations, etc
3. i am using agentic coding to brainstorm on ideas, analyze a feature and then implementing it through different developer agents.
4. i tried doing this with godot because it seemed like a logical choice, but agentic coding & godot lead to terrible results and i burned through 25% tokens without having anything that i could use.
5. i switched to an angular project because using html & css (and canas/three.js) will allow me to implement the UI of the game much faster and much more logical. plus i know this so i can adjust code myself much more easily. the final build will be done in Tauri
6. this will become a steam game only for now, maybe with dlc in the future if it sells well enough

